We’ll have to skip over the juiciest parts for today’s episode, but the point

00:07:11.262 --> 00:07:16.992
is that this was a sixty-year period of fighting between Scotland and England.

00:07:18.302 --> 00:07:22.642
There are no reliable figures for the number of people who died–it’s

00:07:22.662 --> 00:07:27.252
most likely in the tens of thousands–but what is undeniable is

00:07:27.252 --> 00:07:32.432
that this formed the basis of the rivalry that still exists today.

00:07:34.032 --> 00:07:39.782
If you remember “Proud Edward’s Army” from the Scottish national anthem, The Flower of Scotland,

00:07:40.252 --> 00:07:47.482
this was King Edward II, the son of Edward I, the king who had first marched north into Scotland.

00:07:48.842 --> 00:07:53.732
Now, with the wars of Scottish independence over in the late 14th

00:07:53.752 --> 00:07:58.993
century, Scotland and England existed as two separate kingdoms.

00:08:00.572 --> 00:08:06.122
Like all good European rulers, they made sure that alliances and relationships

00:08:06.122 --> 00:08:11.662
with other countries were reinforced through marriage, so Scottish and

00:08:11.682 --> 00:08:16.962
English princesses would be sent off to marry European princes, and European

00:08:16.962 --> 00:08:22.322
princesses would be brought to Britain to marry Scottish and English princes.

00:08:23.472 --> 00:08:30.282
And occasionally English and Scottish royalty would marry, to maintain the peace.

00:08:31.752 --> 00:08:40.212
All well and good, but what happened in the early 17th century, in 1601 to be precise, was

00:08:40.212 --> 00:08:46.452
an event that underlined quite how linked the Scottish and English royal families were.

00:08:47.902 --> 00:08:55.212
Queen Elizabeth I of England died childless, and her closest relation, the next in line to

00:08:55.212 --> 00:09:03.872
the throne was a man called James, who just so happened to be James VI, King of Scotland.

00:09:05.212 --> 00:09:09.412
So, the King of Scotland also became the King of England,

00:09:09.862 --> 00:09:14.892
King James VI of Scotland also became King James I of England.

00:09:16.322 --> 00:09:21.332
This was an event that would bring the two countries together like never before.

00:09:22.182 --> 00:09:25.582
The King of England would, of course, not declare war

00:09:25.592 --> 00:09:28.572
on The King of Scotland because he was the same person.

00:09:30.112 --> 00:09:38.172
Importantly, however, this was not a political union, it was called the Union of The Crowns, meaning

00:09:38.192 --> 00:09:44.862
that the two countries would share the same monarch, but have different laws and political systems.

00:09:45.962 --> 00:09:51.162
It wouldn’t be until 1707 that Scotland and England officially became

00:09:51.172 --> 00:09:56.062
one country, Great Britain, ruled by one parliament and one monarch.

00:09:57.352 --> 00:10:02.702
Now, the British history buffs among you will have realised that I’ve missed out on quite a few

00:10:02.712 --> 00:10:08.092
important things along the way, like the English Civil War and the brief period when neither

00:10:08.102 --> 00:10:13.182
England nor Scotland had a king, and when Bonnie Prince Charlie tried to mount a rebellion

00:10:13.182 --> 00:10:19.262
and overthrow the English king, but for the purposes of today’s episode, we must move on.

00:10:20.612 --> 00:10:30.062
Since 1707, Scotland and England have been united, one country, one currency, ruled by one monarch.

00:10:31.352 --> 00:10:37.392
But perhaps surprisingly, not everything was united, not everything was shared.

00:10:38.332 --> 00:10:44.762
Scotland kept its own religious system, its own education system and its own laws.

00:10:46.062 --> 00:10:50.432
If you have ever spent any time reading the small print of the terms and

00:10:50.432 --> 00:10:55.752
conditions of a UK-registered company, you will often find that it refers

00:10:55.752 --> 00:11:01.022
to “the laws of England and Wales”, not “the laws of the United Kingdom”.

00:11:01.982 --> 00:11:08.312
This is because there is no “UK law”, there are in fact three different legal systems.

00:11:08.912 --> 00:11:14.032
There’s Northern Irish law, and then there is Scottish Law and English law.

00:11:14.972 --> 00:11:20.302
Now, we don’t want to get bogged down in legal jargon, but the point is that England

00:11:20.322 --> 00:11:25.842
and Scotland were united as one country, but there were still important differences.

00:11:26.992 --> 00:11:31.302
And, to state the obvious, just because Scotland and England were now

00:11:31.302 --> 00:11:36.142
united, this didn’t mean that all cultural and regional differences simply

00:11:36.152 --> 00:11:41.642
vanished, and all previous rivalries and memories of past wars were forgotten.

00:11:42.322 --> 00:11:43.102
Far from it.

00:11:43.952 --> 00:11:49.342
Especially in Scotland, people are far more likely, and increasingly

00:11:49.352 --> 00:11:53.552
more likely, to consider themselves Scottish than British.

00:11:54.992 --> 00:12:01.302
